cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

The paper discusses the design of a transceiver for mmWave band mobile communications, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and architecture (cs.AR). The use of large antenna arrays and hybrid analog-digital pre-coding architectures also suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SP) and hardware architecture (cs.AR). However, since the paper primarily focuses on the design of a cognitive transceiver for efficient coexistence with incumbent services, we believe that cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.AR are the most likely sub-categories.
